Butchers in Kimende town, Kiambu county, have threatened to start taking their stock and equipment home after close of business.They said robbers break into their shops and steal plates, weighing machines, gas cylinders and meat.Speaking in Kimende town on Tuesday, subcounty community policing chairman Peter Kiugu said the thieves eat the leftovers, then carry uncooked meat in bags and sufurias. The thieves must be very hungry. They even carry old kitchenware, he said.Kiugu said butchers have complained about losses. Deputy county commissioner Aron Koros said patrols will be intensified.